result.execSummary:
The defendant Christine Ann Stoffel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 15CF104 & 15CF35 called at 10:37 am. Defendant Christine Ann Stoffel in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached.   15CF104-Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Preliminary Hearing and Time Limits discussed. Defendant wishes to waive preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of preliminary hearing. Court finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over. Information filed. Attorney Ulrich confirms receipt, waives formal reading. 15CF35 & 15CF104-State moves to amend Count 1 of 15CF35 to Possess Illegally obtained Rx in violation of 450.11(7)(h).   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: 15CF35-No Contest to Count 1 as amended &  No Contest to Count 2. No Contest to Count 1 of 15CF104. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 2 & 3 of 15CF104.  Statement by defendant. Statement by Court prior to sentencing. Court senteces the defendant to: All Counts- SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. If revoked, 2 days CTS. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through, Maintain absolute sobriety, Not to be on the premises of any bars, Not to possess or ingest any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan, including DNA surcharge.  Court orders bond on file be applied. Appeal Rights.
